{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"alias":"conveyable-tricky-jaguar","description":"## Why\n`test_completion_floor_e2e.py::test_non_regression_floor_is_review_only` asserts, via\n`inspect.getsource` of three private floor functions, that tokens like `sign_manifest`,\n`transition`, `reopen(` are absent, and that `completion_floor` does not appear in a\ndifferent module's source (`:181-198`). An indirect call through a helper or a renamed API\nevades it. VALIDATED as a change-detector; a behavioral replacement is feasible (the file\nalready builds a full `_partial_epic` fixture).\n\n## What\nReplace the source-token assertions with monkeypatch spies around `sign_manifest` /\n`transition` / `reopen` / event-append / file writes, running the floor over the fixture.\n\n## Scope\n- `tests/unit/test_completion_floor_e2e.py`.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Spies assert zero calls to signing/transition/reopen/append and no store mutation\n      escapes the returned verdict dict.\n- [ ] Before/after store + attestation snapshots are unchanged.\n- [ ] Test fails if a signing/transition call is introduced (even via a helper/rename).\n- [ ] `make test` green.","id":"75d9-582d-9a82-4763","parent_id":"bf50-2131-271b-4fdc","priority":2,"tags":["p1","plan-review","change-detector"],"ticket_type":"story","title":"Replace completion-floor review-only source-token test with a spy-based side-effect test"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783784812747954001,"uuid":"21aec5be-3871-4b8b-848e-cb4cb8b629db"}